{
  "text": "hydrogenosomes [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . In many respects, an acceptance that mitochondria are found in all eukaryotes, allowing for extreme variation in metabolic differences and specializations, would be a more reasonable and useful definition for this organelle than the tripartite categorization in common use.",
